org.fcrepo.server.resourceIndex

Class ParamDomainMap

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractMap<K,V>
      • java.util.TreeMap<String,ParamDomain>
        • org.fcrepo.server.resourceIndex.ParamDomainMap
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Cloneable, Map<String,ParamDomain>, NavigableMap<String,ParamDomain>, SortedMap<String,ParamDomain>

    public class ParamDomainMap
extends TreeMap<String,ParamDomain>
    A sorted map of all ParamDomains for a method, keyed by parameter name. As per the SortedMap contract, iterators over the parameter names in this collection will provide the keys in ascending order.
    Author:
    Chris Wilper
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

      • getPermutations

        public Set<String> getPermutations()
        Get all permutations of the method. A "permutation" is a known runtime method invocation, and is formatted as in the following examples:
        • methodName
        • methodName?parm1=val1&parm2=val1
        • methodName?parm1=val1&parm2=val2
        • methodName?parm1=val2&parm2=val1
        • methodName?parm1=val2&parm2=val2
        Returns:
        the set of invokable permutations for the method.
